  "title": "Possible to add custom data attribute & ID in hits template root element?",
  "body": "Hello,\n\nI'd like to put search results into a [Salvattore Masonry Grid](http://salvattore.com/) , but am having trouble getting the \"data-columns\" attribute & element ID added to the \"ais-hits\" root container. \n\nCurrently I'm getting:\n\n``` html\n<div id=\"hits-container\">\n    <div class=\"ais-hits\">\n        <div class=\"ais-hits--item\">ITEM CONTENT<div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n```\n\nWhat I need to acheive is:\n\n``` html\n<div id=\"hits-container\">\n    <div id=\"itemGrid\" class=\"ais-hits\" data-colums>\n        <div class=\"ais-hits--item\">ITEM CONTENT<div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n```\n\nIs this possible?\n\nThanks kindly!\n",
